   28
   29 ## Displacement Rules
   30
   31 ### Rule 1 — Challenger must clear all five criteria
   32 A challenger peak cannot displace the incumbent simply by having a higher score. It must independently satisfy all five qualification criteria
       from WO-1821:
   33 1. Cross-domain convergence (min 2 independent domains)
   34 2. Persistence threshold (min 72h)
   35 3. Velocity direction (building)
   36 4. Counter-signal resistance
   37 5. Hard convergence floor
   38
   39 ### Rule 2 — Incumbent loses designation when criteria fail
   40 The current Happy Path loses its purple designation immediately when any of its five criteria are no longer met — even if no challenger exists
      . An expired Happy Path is not replaced with a lesser candidate. The canvas returns to no-purple state.
   41
   42 ### Rule 3 — Displacement threshold
   43 A challenger must exceed the incumbent's composite qualification score by a minimum margin before displacement fires. This prevents rapid osci
      llation between two near-equal peaks.
   44
   45 - Minimum displacement margin: **[threshold TBD — requires live signal calibration]**
   46 - Below the margin: challenger is noted but does not displace
   47
   48 ### Rule 4 — Hysteresis buffer
   49 Displacement does not fire on a single-frame qualification event. The challenger must hold above the displacement threshold for a minimum buff
      er window before displacement is confirmed.
   50
   51 - Buffer window: **[TBD — likely 15–30 minutes, needs calibration]**
   52 - Prevents noise-driven displacement
